ce:section.ce:para:
A three-electrode EC system has been set up for the synthesis of CQDs (Scheme 1
                        ) Two Pt sheets (1.0cm2) and Ag/AgCl were employed as the working, auxiliary and reference electrodes, respectively. The electrolytes were prepared by adding 5mmol amino acid such as Cys, Asp, Ser, Met, His or Arg, respectively in 10mL ultrapure water containing 3M NH3
                        H2O. A constant potential ranging from 1 to 10V was applied to carry out the EC reaction using a CH Instrument and the amperometric i-t curves were collected. The color of the electrolyte mixture changed from colorless to yellow and then to dark brown in 2h. In order to purify the N-CQDs, the dark brown aqueous solution was subjected to dialysis against ultrapure water through a membrane (MWCO of 3500) for 24h. Finally, either the aqueous suspension of N-CQDs or the vacuum freeze-dried N-CQDs was used for the following characterizations.

The Asp-N-CQDs showed well excitation-dependent PL when coated on cotton fibers and silk fibers, which made them a valuable fluorochrome. For staining test, the cotton fibers and silk fibers were stained with the Asp-N-CQDs suspension, then rinsed with water and dried at 60
                        °C in vacuum oven. Excitation-dependent FL behaviors were observed with the cotton fiber and silk fiber by inverted fluorescence microscope. The silk fiber and cotton fiber exhibited bright green and red fluorescence, respectively, when the excitation wavelength was set at (blue) 450–480nm and (green) 510–550nm, respectively (Fig. 9
                        ). This result indicated that the as-prepared Asp-N-CQDs had great application potentials as biocompatible staining reagent.
